# Users

The Users page provides a full management interface for user accounts. It is accessible
only to **site admins** (`SysadminRoute` guard). Admins can create, edit, and permanently
delete users, as well as filter the list by company affiliation.

A user's effective role shown in the grid is derived from their relationships in the
system — an `admin`-role user who also has an `Owner` record is displayed as **Owner**,
and a `user`-role user linked to a manager employee record is displayed as **Manager**,
taking precedence over the base `role` field.

---

## Access Control

| Action      | Who        |
| ----------- | ---------- |
| View list   | Admin only |
| Create user | Admin only |
| Edit user   | Admin only |
| Delete user | Admin only |

Route `/users` is wrapped in `SysadminRoute`, which redirects non-admins to the home page.

---

## Data Model

Defined in `client/src/types/User.model.ts`.

### `User`

| Field           | Type             | Notes                                                      |
| --------------- | ---------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------- |
| `id`            | `string`         | UUID                                                       |
| `email`         | `string`         |                                                            |
| `firstName`     | `string`         |                                                            |
| `lastName`      | `string`         |                                                            |
| `avatar`        | `string?`        |                                                            |
| `phoneNumber`   | `string \| null` |                                                            |
| `address`       | `string \| null` |                                                            |
| `country`       | `string \| null` |                                                            |
| `role`          | `string`         | `"admin"` \| `"user"`                                      |
| `status`        | `string`         | `"active"` \| `"inactive"` \| `"suspended"` \| `"pending"` |
| `emailVerified` | `boolean`        |                                                            |
| `lastLoginAt`   | `string \| null` | ISO timestamp                                              |
| `createdAt`     | `string`         |                                                            |
| `updatedAt`     | `string`         |                                                            |
| `isOwner`       | `boolean`        | `true` when a linked `Owner` record exists                 |
| `isManager`     | `boolean`        | `true` when the user's employee record is a manager        |

### Enums

```
UserRole:   admin | user
UserStatus: active | inactive | suspended | pending
```

---

## API

### Client (`client/src/api/userApi.ts`)

| Method     | Endpoint            | Description                                                              |
| ---------- | ------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| `list()`   | `GET /users`        | Paginated list; supports `search`, `role`, `status`, `companyId` filters |
| `get(id)`  | `GET /users/:id`    | Single user detail                                                       |
| `create()` | `POST /users`       | Create a new user with hashed password                                   |
| `update()` | `PUT /users/:id`    | Partial update of any editable field                                     |
| `remove()` | `DELETE /users/:id` | Permanently delete a user                                                |

### TanStack Query Hooks (`client/src/api/useUser.tsx`)

| Hook                | Purpose                                           |
| ------------------- | ------------------------------------------------- |
| `useUsers(params?)` | Paginated, filterable user list                   |
| `useUser(id)`       | Single user detail                                |
| `useCreateUser()`   | Mutation; invalidates list on success             |
| `useUpdateUser()`   | Mutation; invalidates list + detail on success    |
| `useDeleteUser()`   | Mutation; invalidates list + removes detail cache |

---

## Components

### `Users.tsx`

Main page component. Manages modal open/close state for create, edit, and delete.

- **Search**: debounced (300 ms), searches by name or email.
- **Company filter**: dropdown populated from `useCompanies()` (admin-only endpoint
  returning all companies); filters the user list to those associated with a given company.
- Both filters are combined and passed as query params to `useUsers()`.
- The **New User** button is always visible (page is admin-only).

### `Users.columns.tsx`

AG Grid column definitions.

| Column   | Field           | Notes                                                                                  |
| -------- | --------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Name     | computed        | `firstName + lastName`; flex, min 160 px                                               |
| Email    | `email`         | Flex, min 200 px                                                                       |
| Role     | `role`          | Badge with priority: **Owner** (violet) → **Manager** (indigo) → base role (blue/gray) |
| Status   | `status`        | Badge: green / yellow / red / gray                                                     |
| Verified | `emailVerified` | Dot badge: green = verified, gray = unverified                                         |
| Created  | `createdAt`     | Formatted as locale date string                                                        |
| Actions  | —               | Pinned right; Edit (pencil) + Delete (trash, red)                                      |

### `Modals/CreateUserModal.tsx`

Uses `react-hook-form`. Fields:

| Field      | Required       | Default  |
| ---------- | -------------- | -------- |
| First name | No             | —        |
| Last name  | No             | —        |
| Email      | Yes            | —        |
| Password   | Yes (≥8 chars) | —        |
| Role       | No             | `user`   |
| Status     | No             | `active` |

### `Modals/EditUserModal.tsx`

Pre-populates from the selected `User` via `useEffect`. Editable fields:

- First name, Last name, Email, Phone number
- Role (`admin` / `user`)
- Status (`active` / `pending` / `suspended` / `inactive`)
- Email verified (checkbox)

### `Modals/DeleteUserModal.tsx`

Confirmation dialog showing the user's full name and email. Deletion is **permanent**
and irreversible. Calls `useDeleteUser()` on confirm.
